estrianism, and efficient automobilism, is complicated. Thus, the liberal newspapers’ promotion of a city of orderly infrastructure and contented people in actual Toronto proved strikingly illiberal. Consequently, Mackintosh’s study reveals the contradictory nature of newspapers and the historiographical complexities of newspaper research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aPresszOntariozTorontoxHistoryy19th century. 0aPresszOntariozTorontoxHistoryy20th century. 0aStreetszOntariozTorontoxDesign and constructionxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Historical Geography.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066594940uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978144266656640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781442666566423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781442666566.jpg  a978-3-11-066594-9  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles